I remember receiving letters from school kids, and a six month subscription to the Chicago Tribune from a man I never knew. I sent him a thank you. Never heard from him again.<br><br>
Lots of times we didn't get our mail regularly. When it arrived, there would often be 3 or 4 Tribunes in the mail for me. So, many of the guys in C company would be sitting around reading different sections. Newspapers everywhere. I can envision ol' Charley spying us and saying, &quot;Dier must have gotten his Tribs today.&quot;<br><br>
The packages and the love you sent will always be remembered and appreciated. Thanks.<br><br>
